  "text": "Thirdly, the 18 % of men and 19 % of women that undertook some but not a sufficient number of sessions of MS sport and exercise activities per week are targets where successful intervention may be more likely. If related to the trans-theoretical model, then these individuals could be considered to be in the 'maintenance' phase (i.e. already undertaking a relevant behaviour) [CITATION_1] . It is potentially easier for them to increase the frequency of this behaviour to the recommended levels than for those not currently undertaking any to start.",
